	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />First is a non-looped 17-byte sample, second is looped. First byte is a short "hill", the next bytes make larger "hills". All 17 bytes are looped. Recording and code:
<br /><img src="http://e.imagehost.org/0647/dmc_loop.png" alt="Image" />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">lda #1&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; length = 17 bytes<br />sta $4013<br /><br />; Play unlooped<br />lda #$0C<br />sta $4010<br />lda #$10<br />sta $4015<br />delay_msec 15<br /><br />; Play looped<br />lda #$4C<br />sta $4010<br />lda #$10<br />sta $4015<br />delay_msec 30<br /><br />sample:<br />.byte $0F<br />.byte $FF,$00,$FF,$00,$FF,$00,$FF,$00<br />.byte $FF,$00,$FF,$00,$FF,$00,$FF,$00<br /></div>

		

